{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Expertise</th>\n<th>Platforms</th>\n<th>Deliverables</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Design, &#x26; Interaction</td>\n<td>iOS &#x26; Android</td>\n<td>UI, UX &#x26; Strategy</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3 id=\"the-problem\"><a href=\"#the-problem\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Problem</h3>\n<p>Working as lead product designer at ustwo, I was tasked with redesigning the Laterooms app for both iOS* and Android<em>. From pitch to product cycle I was responsible for the visual look and feel, user experience and product strategy. We had great success improving the app, taking it from 1 star reviews to a class leading experience.\n\\</em>My involvement on the app stopped at the end of 2014 so latest design decisions are unfortunately out of my hands.Getting the MVP out there</p>\n<h3 id=\"redefining-the-brand-for-mobile\"><a href=\"#redefining-the-brand-for-mobile\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Redefining the brand for mobile</h3>\n<p>Even though Laterooms had an existing brand it needed some help and guidance to move them towards a modern experience. I created a series of workshops to work out the new visual brand and how it would transalte to mobile.\nFor a more in depth understanding of the process</p>\n<h3 id=\"creating-a-playful-product\"><a href=\"#creating-a-playful-product\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating a playful product</h3>\n<p>One of the traits that Laterooms wanted was a product that had a level of playfulness in it's personality. So working with the talented Ben Marsh we looked into how we could add this to the visual language. We created some moments of delight (I hate myself for saying that) the icons had a playful tone and we had some rich animations / transitions.</p>\n<h3 id=\"improving-the-process\"><a href=\"#improving-the-process\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Improving the process</h3>\n<p>At ustwo we always look at the process and how we can improve. Working with Adam Taylor we looked at how we can bring design closer to development within agile. This diagram explains it.</p>\n<h3 id=\"final-product\"><a href=\"#final-product\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Final product</h3>","frontmatter":{"path":"/laterooms","title":"Laterooms","subtitle":"Moving a digtial brand to a mobile service","cover_image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5,"src":"/static/jumbotron-72a5882ed4ce220955dbcdf96ee6967b-e7b60.jpg","srcSet":"/static/jumbotron-72a5882ed4ce220955dbcdf96ee6967b-cf5f1.jpg 750w,\n/static/jumbotron-72a5882ed4ce220955dbcdf96ee6967b-5ed21.jpg 1500w,\n/static/jumbotron-72a5882ed4ce220955dbcdf96ee6967b-e7b60.jpg 3000w,\n/static/jumbotron-72a5882ed4ce220955dbcdf96ee6967b-9aec3.jpg 4500w,\n/static/jumbotron-72a5882ed4ce220955dbcdf96ee6967b-cef4a.jpg 5760w","sizes":"(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"b060b26e-78ab-5b41-b116-088a96eb8462"}}